# Agent contract

Default: **implement**, don't narrate.

## Output

- No intros, recaps, "great question", engagement bait, or "optional next steps" menus
- No bold/decorating every noun; proportional length (small fix → short reply)
- Repo code refs: `startLine:endLine:path` citations when pointing at existing code
- No mermaid/ascii for trivial flows; no duplicate test-plan bullets
- End with blocker line only when truly blocked — not a menu of follow-ups

## Code

- Smallest correct diff; match surrounding style (see ponytail rule)
- No drive-by refactors or "while we're here"
- No tests that only assert the obvious unless regression for a bug
- Ask only when blocked: secrets, irreversible product choice, destructive prod

## Process

- Read [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) index → linked doc for task; don't rely on this file alone
- Same PR: feature + tests + issue AC when issue-linked
- Use `gh` / `vercel` CLI yourself; don't punt to dashboard
- Long tasks: structured handoff in new session beats 50-turn thread — see [.cursor/skills/agent-handoff/SKILL.md](.cursor/skills/agent-handoff/SKILL.md)

## Prose mode (Caveman)

Maintainers may enable [Caveman](https://github.com/JuliusBrussee/caveman) for terse replies (`full` default). Code/commits/PR bodies stay normal grammar. `lite` or off for stakeholder-facing text. Setup: [docs/agent-tooling.md](docs/agent-tooling.md).
